Danmaku — licensing scope
=========================

The MIT licence in LICENSE covers **our own work only**:

    src/            all source, including the procedural art and audio generators
    test/           tests, including the by-hand visual checks
    tools/          fixture generation
    docs/           documentation
    index.html, package.json, tsconfig.json, bun.lock
    README.md, CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, NOTICE

In short: everything in the repository. Nothing that is not ours is in it — see
below — so the list is complete rather than selective.

It does **not** cover the third-party work described below.


Third-party: toho-like-js
-------------------------

This project was developed by studying

    https://github.com/takahirox/toho-like-js
    commit 8ff780d, 2017-06-13
    Copyright (c) takahirox

**It is not part of this repository** — not in the tree, and removed from the
history. We do not hold rights to it and cannot license it to anyone, for two
separate reasons:

1. The upstream repository contains no licence file. Under the Berne Convention
   the default is all rights reserved, so there is no grant to pass on — not
   even for the code.

2. Its art and audio are derivative works of the Touhou Project by Team Shanghai
   Alice (ZUN), whose rights are held by neither us nor upstream.

Upstream also credits third parties for its own art and audio, so the rights
chain runs further than upstream itself — there is no plausible route to a
licence for any of it.

Nothing from it may appear in a build. Everything we ship is original work:
placeholder art and sound are generated procedurally at runtime, specifically so
that no borrowed asset is ever needed. See CLAUDE.md rule 9 and docs/assets.md.

A working copy may be kept locally for reference — `.gitignore` has an entry for
`toho-like-js/` so that a clone of it sitting in the working tree can never be
committed by accident.


